The paper deals with combinatorial objects and algorithmic problems related to hyperplane arrangements, topological orderings, and acyclic orientations. These topics are closely related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and combinatorics (cs.DS). The paper also discusses graph theory concepts such as shortest paths and closed orientations, which fall under the category of graph theory (cs.GT) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
